sub_title: Future master student Biobased Materials at Maastricht University | Recently graduated bachelor (BSc) student Applied Science at Zuyd University of Applied Sciences
summary:
In September, I will start the master Biobased Materials at Maastricht university.

Recently graduated student Applied Science who is interested in organic chemistry. During my education, I found out that the beta sciences have a lot in common with each other. I learned about analytical chemistry, inorganic chemistry, materials, engineering, processing techniques and the biological field, next to organic chemistry. During my internship and minor, this knowledge was really useful and I hope I can use it again in my next challenge.

Feel free to contact me!
bjornserra@gmail.com
